  <rte>
    <name>Causey Pike from Stoneycroft, nr. Braithwaite</name>
    <desc>Causey Pike is of modest height yet its distinctive summit makes it easily recognised from the area around Derwentwater and Keswick. Topped by five knuckles not dissimilar to a clenched fist, it immediately throws out a challenge to be climbed.</desc>
    <author>Copyright Walking Britain</author>
	<url>www.walkingbritain.co.uk/walk-1155-description</url>
